## STAGE 1 — NUMBERING (no gaps, no duplicates)

- [ ] revision-express.md questions numbered sequentially
- [ ] Course files index in README.md matches actual files on disk
- [ ] Modules in 00-programme.md numbered sequentially
- [ ] Axes in suivi-progression.md numbered sequentially

## STAGE 2 — COUNTS MATCH

- [ ] Validated concepts count in memory matches completed modules in 00-programme.md
- [ ] Course files listed in README.md = actual course files on disk
- [ ] Questions count in README.md = last question number in revision-express.md

## STAGE 3 — CROSS-FILE CONSISTENCY

- [ ] Module statuses match across 00-programme.md, README.md, and memory
- [ ] Each completed module has: course file + revision questions + progress axis entry
- [ ] Weakness levels match between suivi-progression.md and memory
- [ ] Memory state reflects current session accurately

## STAGE 4 — COMPLETENESS

- [ ] Every axis in suivi-progression.md has a sub-concepts TABLE
- [ ] Every course file has required sections (header, summary, prerequisites)
- [ ] No TODO or placeholder text in tracking files

## STAGE 5 — TIMESTAMPS

- [ ] All "Derniere mise a jour" dates = today's date during active session
